From 16d1f4640439bdf84f842e075ce6def589e2f94e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Terence Tritton <ttritton@google.com>
Date: Thu, 29 May 2025 11:03:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ANDROID: Define NSEC_PER_SEC as long long

NSEC_PER_SEC is a long which casues overflow issues or arm32.
Defined as long long to stop overflow.

Bug: 422759683
Change-Id: I58f77306ca3f850d6e4ab4930937ce9dcf8a5dd5
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/all/20250805162153.952693-1-wakel@google.com/
Signed-off-by: Wake Liu <wakel@google.com>
Test: atest vts_linux_kselftest_arm_32:timers_set-timer-lat_arm_32
---
 include/vdso/time64.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/vdso/time64.h b/include/vdso/time64.h
index b40cfa2aa33c8..07641b27d139a 100644
--- a/include/vdso/time64.h
+++ b/include/vdso/time64.h
@@ -8,7 +8,7 @@
 #define NSEC_PER_USEC	1000L
 #define NSEC_PER_MSEC	1000000L
 #define USEC_PER_SEC	1000000L
-#define NSEC_PER_SEC	1000000000L
+#define NSEC_PER_SEC	1000000000LL
 #define PSEC_PER_SEC	1000000000000LL
 #define FSEC_PER_SEC	1000000000000000LL
 
